.define('lazy_copy_file', function(require, exports, module) {
    return lazy_copy_file(exports, module);
});
Q:

Change / rename folder or text file automatically

I have a file with a directory name and a name that I want to rename it. The file name is "file1.txt".
Is there a way to change the file name without changing the file name? 
I need it to be the same on every file.
How can I change the file name without changing the file?
The files are as follows:
enter.txt
file1.txt

A:

You can rename the file name using eval.
import { File, FileWriter } from 'lazy_copy_file';
import { lazy_copy_file } from 'lazy_copy_file';

export function renameFile(fileName: string) {
    // ...
}

var g = new lazy_copy_file(['file1.txt']);
g.renameFile(fileName);

console.log(g.renameFile(fileName));

Edit:
Thanks Mark for the answer.
You can also use the file path to rename the file name in the console.
var g = new lazy_copy_file(['file1.txt']);
g.renameFile(fileName);

console.log(g.renameFile(fileName));

